 <item> <title>Statement from U.S. Education Secretary Arne Duncan on commitments from the Council of Chief State School Officers and the Council of the Great City Schools on high-quality assessments:</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/statement-us-education-secretary-arne-duncan-commitments-council-chief-state-school-officers-and-council-great-city-schools-high-quality-assessments</link>
 <description>“Educators, parents, and policy makers need to know how much students are learning; that’s why thoughtful assessment of student learning and student growth, including annual assessments, is a vital part of progress in education. Assessments must be of high quality, and must make good use of educators’ and students’ time.</description>
